summary: An Ordinance accepting a deed from the Weyerhaeuser Timber Company, a corporation, duly incorporated under the laws of the State of Washington, to The City of Seattle , dated the 26th day of March, in the year of our Lord Nineteen Hundred and Seventeen to the following described land situated in the County of King, State of Washington, to-wit: All of Section Thirty-three (33) in township Twenty-three (23) North, of Range Eight (8) East, W. M. containing six hundred and forty (640) acres, more or less; and appropriating Nine Hundred Eighty ($980) Dollars in payment therefor from the Cedar River Water Shed Condemnation Fund.
